Complexity Analysis
Time Complexity

At every iteration, half of the search space is discarded.

n → n/2 → n/4 → n/8 ...

Therefore:

Time Complexity = O(log n)
Space Complexity

Only a few variables are used.

Space Complexity = O(1)
Pattern Recognition

Use this Binary Search pattern when:

✅ Array is sorted

✅ Need to find an element or its position

✅ Need to determine where an element should be inserted

✅ Problem asks for O(log n) complexity

Core Idea

If the target is found, return its index.
If not found, low automatically ends up at the correct insertion position.
